Algorithmic Trading on BTC¶

Objective¶

This notebook implements an algorithmic trading strategy for Bitcoin (BTC). The workflow includes:

  • Loading and preparing the data
  • Performing exploratory data analysis (EDA)
  • Implementing a trading strategy
  • Evaluating the performance of the strategy

1. Importing Libraries¶

We start by importing necessary libraries for data manipulation, visualization, and backtesting.

In [57]:
df_BTC = pd.merge(df_BTC, df_BTC_trend[['Date', 'Google Trend']], on= 'Date', how='left')
df_BTC = pd.merge(df_BTC, df_BTC_Reddit[['Date', 'Score', 'Score Info']], on= 'Date', how='left')
df_BTC = pd.merge(df_BTC, dxy_data[['Date', 'DXY Log return']], on= 'Date', how='left')
df_BTC['DXY Log return'] = df_BTC['DXY Log return'].ffill()

df_BTC['Score Lag 1D'] = df_BTC['Score'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['Score Lag 5D'] = df_BTC['Score'].shift(-5)
df_BTC['Score Lag 1D Dummy'] = df_BTC['Score Lag 1D'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x != 50 else 0)
df_BTC['Score Lag 5D Dummy'] = df_BTC['Score Lag 5D'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x != 50 else 0)
df_BTC['Weighted Score Lag 1D'] = df_BTC['Score Lag 1D'] * df_BTC['Score Lag 1D Dummy']
df_BTC['Weighted Score Lag 5D'] = df_BTC['Score Lag 5D'] * df_BTC['Score Lag 5D Dummy']
df_BTC['EMA_12'] = df_BTC['Clôture'].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()
df_BTC['EMA_26'] = df_BTC['Clôture'].ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()
df_BTC['MACD'] = df_BTC['EMA_12'] - df_BTC['EMA_26']
df_BTC['Signal Line'] = df_BTC['MACD'].ewm(span=9, adjust=False).mean()
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['Google Trend'])
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=["RSI (20)"])
df_BTC['Log Return'] = np.log(df_BTC['Clôture'] / df_BTC['Ouvt'])
df_BTC['EMA_12_returns'] = df_BTC['Log Return'].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()
df_BTC['EMA_26_returns'] = df_BTC['Log Return'].ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()
df_BTC['MACD_returns'] = df_BTC['EMA_12_returns'] - df_BTC['EMA_26_returns']
df_BTC['Mvt After Close'] = np.log(df_BTC['Ouvt'] / df_BTC['Clôture'].shift(1))
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['Log Return'])
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['Mvt After Close'])
df_BTC['Google Trend'] = df_BTC['Google Trend'].replace('<1', '1')
df_BTC['Google Trend'] = pd.to_numeric(df_BTC['Google Trend'], errors='coerce')
df_BTC['Intraday Variation'] = ((df_BTC['Haut'] - df_BTC['Bas']) / df_BTC['Bas'])
df_BTC['Variation Intraday Veille'] = df_BTC['Intraday Variation'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['MACD_returns_RSI_interaction'] = df_BTC['MACD_returns'] * df_BTC['RSI (10)']
df_BTC['RSI Info'] = df_BTC['RSI (10)'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x > 70 else (-1 if x < 30 else 0))
df_BTC['MACD_returns Lag 1'] = df_BTC['MACD_returns'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['Google Trend Lag 1'] = df_BTC['Google Trend'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['RSI Lag 1'] = df_BTC['RSI (10)'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['Date correspondante au Lag 1'] = df_BTC['Date'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['MACD_returns_RSI_interaction Lag 1'] = df_BTC['MACD_returns_RSI_interaction'].shift(-1)
df_BTC['DXY Log return Lag 1D'] = df_BTC['DXY Log return'].shift(-1)


df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['Variation Intraday Veille'])
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['Score Info'])
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['Score Lag 5D'])
df_BTC = df_BTC.dropna(subset=['RSI Lag 1'])

df_BTC = df_BTC.iloc[::-1].reset_index(drop=True)

5. Backtesting the Strategy¶

We apply the strategy to historical data and assess its performance:

  • Calculate returns
  • Track trade execution
  • Measure profitability
In [61]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# Préparation des données
#X = df_BTC[['Mvt After Close', 'MACD_returns Lag 1', 'RSI Lag 1', 'MACD_returns_RSI_interaction Lag 1', 'Score Lag 1D Dummy', 'Google Trend Lag 1', 'DXY Log return Lag 1D']]
X = df_BTC[['MACD_returns Lag 1', 'RSI Lag 1', 'MACD_returns_RSI_interaction Lag 1', 'Weighted Score Lag 1D', 'Google Trend Lag 1', 'DXY Log return Lag 1D']]
y = df_BTC['Log Return']

# Supprimer les lignes avec des valeurs manquantes
X = X.dropna()
y = y[X.index]

scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

split_index = int(0.8 * len(X_scaled))
# Diviser les données en ensemble d'entraînement et ensemble de test
X_train, X_test = X_scaled[:split_index], X_scaled[split_index:]
y_train, y_test = y[:split_index], y[split_index:]

# Initialiser le modèle de régression linéaire
model = LinearRegression()

# Entraîner le modèle
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Faire des prédictions sur l'ensemble de test
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

# Évaluation du modèle
print("Évaluation du modèle:")
print(f"MSE: {mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)}")
print(f"RMSE: {np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))}")
print(f"MAE: {mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)}")
print(f"R²: {r2_score(y_test, y_pred)}")
print("Coefficients :", model.coef_)
print("Intercept :", model.intercept_)

# Visualiser les prédictions vs les valeurs réelles
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(y_test.values, label='Log Return Réels', color='blue')
plt.plot(y_pred, label='Log Return Prédits', color='red', linestyle='--')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Prédiction des Log Returns avec Régression Linéaire')
plt.xlabel('Index')
plt.ylabel('Log Return')
plt.show()

# Stratégie de trading basée sur les prédictions du modèle
#df_BTC.loc[y_test.index, 'Trading Signal'] = np.where(y_pred > 0, 1, -1)
df_BTC.loc[y_test.index, 'Trading Signal'] = np.where(y_pred > 0.012, 1, np.where(y_pred < -0.012, -1, 0))

# Tracer les signaux de trading et les log returns
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(df_BTC['Log Return'], label='Log Return Réels', color='blue')
plt.plot(df_BTC.index, df_BTC['Trading Signal'] * 0.01, label='Signaux de Trading', color='orange', linestyle='--')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Log Returns vs Signaux de Trading')
plt.xlabel('Index')
plt.ylabel('Log Return')
plt.show()

6. Evaluating Performance¶

We evaluate key performance metrics such as:

  • Profit and loss (PnL)
  • Sharpe ratio
  • Win/loss ratio
In [62]:
# Récapitulatif des trades : dates, prix d'entrée, prix de sortie, PnL

trades = []
trades_long_only = []
trades_hold = []
position_open = False
pnl = 1
pnl_btc_long_only = 1
pnl_hold_BTC = 1
for i in range(len(X_train), len(df_BTC)):
    if df_BTC['Trading Signal'].iloc[i] == 1 and not position_open:
        # Entrée
        position_open = True
        type_trade = 'Long'
        entry_price = df_BTC['Ouvt'].iloc[i]
        entry_price = entry_price * 1.006
        entry_date = df_BTC['Date'].iloc[i]
        exit_price = df_BTC['Clôture'].iloc[i] 
        exit_date = df_BTC['Date'].iloc[i]
        exit_price = exit_price * 0.994
        trade_result = (exit_price - entry_price)/entry_price  # PnL
        trade_direction = 'Gagnant' if trade_result > 0 else 'Perdant'
        pnl += pnl * trade_result

        position_open = False  # Fermer la position

    elif df_BTC['Trading Signal'].iloc[i] == -1 and not position_open:
        # Entrée
        position_open = True
        type_trade = 'Short'
        entry_price = df_BTC['Ouvt'].iloc[i]
        entry_price = entry_price * 0.994
        entry_date = df_BTC['Date'].iloc[i]
        exit_price = df_BTC['Clôture'].iloc[i] 
        exit_date = df_BTC['Date'].iloc[i]
        exit_price = exit_price * 1.006
        trade_result = (entry_price - exit_price)/exit_price  # PnL
        trade_direction = 'Gagnant' if trade_result > 0 else 'Perdant'
        pnl += pnl * trade_result

        position_open = False  # Fermer la position
    
    elif df_BTC['Trading Signal'].iloc[i] == 0 and not position_open:
        position_open = True
        type_trade = 'No Trade'
        entry_price = 0
        entry_price = 0
        entry_date = df_BTC['Date'].iloc[i]
        exit_price = 0 
        exit_date = df_BTC['Date'].iloc[i]
        exit_price = 0
        trade_result = 0
        trade_direction = 'No Trade'
        pnl = pnl

        position_open = False  # Fermer la position
    
    if i == len(X_train):
        entry_price_2 = df_BTC['Ouvt'].iloc[i]
        exit_price_2 = df_BTC['Clôture'].iloc[i]
        btc_long_only = pnl_btc_long_only*(exit_price_2 - entry_price_2*1.006)/(entry_price_2*1.006)
    elif i == len(df_BTC):
        entry_price_2 = df_BTC['Ouvt'].iloc[i]
        exit_price_2 = df_BTC['Clôture'].iloc[i]
        btc_long_only = pnl_btc_long_only*(exit_price_2*0.994 - entry_price_2)/(entry_price_2)
    else:
        entry_price_2 = df_BTC['Ouvt'].iloc[i]
        exit_price_2 = df_BTC['Clôture'].iloc[i]
        btc_long_only = pnl_btc_long_only*(exit_price_2 - entry_price_2)/(entry_price_2)
    
    pnl_btc_long_only += pnl_btc_long_only * btc_long_only
    
    trades.append({
            'Type Trade': type_trade,
            'Date d\'entrée': entry_date,
            'Date de sortie': exit_date,
            'Prix d\'achat': entry_price,
            'Prix de vente': exit_price,
            'Trade': trade_direction,
            'PnL du trade' : trade_result,
            'PnL de la stratégie': pnl,
            'Long Only' : pnl_btc_long_only
        })


# Convertir la liste des trades en DataFrame
trades_df = pd.DataFrame(trades)


# Afficher le récapitulatif des trades
print(trades_df)

# Calculer le PnL cumulé
trades_df['Cumulative PnL'] = trades_df['PnL de la stratégie']

# Plot du PnL cumulé après chaque trade

plt.legend()

# Calculer le pourcentage de trades gagnants
winning_trades = trades_df[trades_df['PnL du trade'] > 0]
losing_trades = trades_df[trades_df['PnL du trade'] < 0]
percentage_winning_trades = len(winning_trades) / (len(winning_trades)+len(losing_trades)) * 100

average_profit_loss = trades_df['PnL du trade'].mean()

average_profit_loss_Long_Only = trades_df['Long Only'].mean()
